text:
1975 introduced new wheel/brake fairings and the Skylane II with improved avionics.  1976 introduced a new 230 hp (172 kW) Continental O-470-S engine, as well as improved wing root fairings.  Certified on 8 October 1971.  4,371 total built; 621 (1972), 1,040 (1973), 1,010 (1974), 820 (1975), and 880 (1976), plus 25 built in France by Reims Aviation in 1976 as the F182P.  In 1976, Cessna stopped offering the baseline 182, and all subsequent models carried the "Skylane" name.
182Q Skylane
Introduced for the 1977 model year with a new 230 hp (172 kW) Continental O-470-U engine and instrument panel fasteners, as well as minor changes to the instrument panel.
